    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "We are able to trigger a memory leak when assigning an numpy array into a `cdef np.ndarray[]` variable. \r\n\r\nPlease see the valgrind report here\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/scipy/scipy/issues/7829\r\n\r\nHere is the relevant code segment. If the commented out line is enabled we detect the leak.\r\n\r\n```\r\n    def __init__(cKDTree self, data, np.intp_t leafsize=16, compact_nodes=True,ùÑæ\r\n            copy_data=False, balanced_tree=True, boxsize=None):\r\n        # cdef np.ndarray[np.float64_t, ndim=2] data_arr\r\n        cdef np.float64_t *tmp\r\n        cdef int _median, _compact\r\n        cdef np.ndarray[np.float64_t, ndim=1] boxsize_arr\r\n        data_arr = np.ascontiguousarray(data, dtype=np.float64)\r\n        if copy_data and (data_arr is data):\r\n            data_arr = data_arr.copy()\r\n        self.data = data_arr\r\n        self.n = data_arr.shape[0]\r\n        self.m = data_arr.shape[1]\r\n        self.leafsize = leafsize\r\n        if self.leafsize<1:\r\n```\r\n\r\nCython version 0.26, running on Python 3.5.3 debug build with numpy 1.13.1.\r\n",
    "closed_at": "2017-09-18T19:01:38Z",
    "comment_data": [
