            "author_association": "OWNER",
            "body": "Quick check: can you confirm that this still happens with 0.26.1?\r\nDoes it only happen when a copy is created, or always? (i.e. is the `.copy()` call needed for reproducing?)\r\nWhat happens if you avoid the double buffer unpacking in the copy case like this:\r\n```\r\ncdef np.ndarray[np.float64_t, ndim=2] data_arr\r\nd = np.ascontiguousarray(data, dtype=np.float64)\r\ndata_arr = d.copy() if copy_data and (d is data) else d\r\n```\r\n(That's preferable anyway, because unpacking buffers isn't for free.)",
